          <p>Most transfers between Atlas users land instantly. Bank transfers in supported instant rails (RTP, FedNow, UPI, PIX, FPS, SEPA Instant) typically arrive in seconds. Where instant rails aren't available, we show the exact arrival time before you confirm — and we never quote a range we can't hit.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What's the catch on the exchange rate?</summary>
          <p>There isn't one. We use the mid-market rate — the same one you'd see on a finance site — and charge a separate, itemized fee. You see the fee, the rate, and the recipient's amount before you confirm.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What if I send money to the wrong person?</summary>
          <p>One tap to request a return inside the app. If the recipient hasn't claimed the money yet, we cancel it instantly. If they have, we'll help you recover it under our buyer/sender protection policy.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Is my money insured?</summary>
          <p>Customer balances are held in segregated, FDIC-insured accounts (US) or equivalent supervised partners in other jurisdictions, up to the applicable per-customer limit. We publish the exact partner and protection level for each market we operate in.</p>
